# Admin View Walkthrough

I have successfully added a premium administrative interface for logging in and creating courses. The implementation follows senior backend developer best practices, ensuring security (CSP compliance), scalability (externalized logic), and a high-end user experience.

## Changes Made

### 1. Backend Updates
-   **[app.js](file:///c:/Users/USER%201/Desktop/backend/app.js)**: Configured the server to serve static files from the `public` directory using `express.static`.

### 2. Admin Interface (Frontend)
-   **[index.html](file:///c:/Users/USER%201/Desktop/backend/public/admin/index.html)**: A sleek login page with Glassmorphism effects and Inter typography.
-   **[dashboard.html](file:///c:/Users/USER%201/Desktop/backend/public/admin/dashboard.html)**: A modern dashboard with a course registration form and an active courses table.
-   **[admin-style.css](file:///c:/Users/USER%201/Desktop/backend/public/admin/css/admin-style.css)**: Centralized styles for the administrative UI, featuring premium gradients and responsive layouts.

### 3. Logic & Security
-   **[admin-logic.js](file:///c:/Users/USER%201/Desktop/backend/public/admin/js/admin-logic.js)**: Shared utilities for authentication checking and JWT handling.
-   **[login.js](file:///c:/Users/USER%201/Desktop/backend/public/admin/js/login.js)**: Externalized login logic to comply with strict Content Security Policy (CSP).
-   **[dashboard.js](file:///c:/Users/USER%201/Desktop/backend/public/admin/js/dashboard.js)**: Externalized dashboard logic for course management.

